Lde/ecspride/FieldSensitivity1;->setTain: In this method, user personal data (specifically the SIM serial number) is originated and stored within a custom object of type Lde/ecspride/Datacontainer. The method retrieves the SIM serial number from the TelephonyManager service using the 'phone' system service identifier. This sensitive information is then set as part of the same custom object, ensuring that it remains tainted throughout its lifecycle in this object.
